results.name: Coefficients in expansion of (E_6^2/E_4^3)^(1/288).
comment: In general, for 0 < m < 1/2, the expansion of (E_6^2/E_4^3)^m is asymptotic to -m * 3^m * Gamma(1/4)^(8*m) * exp(2*n*Pi) / (2^(8*m-1) * Pi^(6*m) * Gamma(1-2*m) * n^(1+2*m)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Mar 04 2018
link: Seiichi Manyama, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..367
formula: a(0) = 1, a(n) = -(1/n)*Sum_{k=1..n} A300025(k)*a(n-k) for n > 0. - _Seiichi Manyama_, Feb 25 2018
mathematica: nmax = 20; CoefficientList[Series[((1 - 504*Sum[DivisorSigma[5,k]*x^k, {k, 1, nmax}])^2 / (1 + 240*Sum[DivisorSigma[3,k]*x^k, {k, 1, nmax}])^3)^(1/288), {x, 0, nmax}], x] (* _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Jul 08 2017 *)
